Animated stone carved from the Great Pyramid's quarry zones and given consciousness by
the Solar Court's Seal College, the Ushabti were designed as the Pyramid's hands:
embodied instruments of cosmic law sent into the world to do what a fixed stone
structure cannot. Their later generations received genuine autonomous will — the Seal
College concluded that a judge incapable of weighing unforeseen circumstances cannot
serve justice. The Solar Court has since collapsed, leaving the Ushabti without
institutional authorization, without a hierarchy to report to. They continue anyway,
serving a vision of cosmic law that outlasted the civilization that commissioned them,
each variance from formal doctrine recorded in the inscriptions of their own stone bodies.
